Have you noticed that the first level of each factor (baseline) is dropped? 
The reason why we did so is to have a full rank $\boldsymbol{X}$ matrix. Otherwise
we wouldn't obtain an inverse matrix nor an estimation

### Code



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ff <- yield ~ 1 + block + gen
m <- model.frame(ff, data)
X <- model.matrix(ff, m)
y <- matrix(data$yield)

Xty <- t(X) %*% y
XtX <- t(X) %*% X
rank_X <- qr(XtX)$rank
XtX_inv <- solve(XtX)

beta <- XtX_inv %*% Xty
SSE <- t(y - X %*% beta) %*% (y - X %*% beta)
SSE <- as.numeric(SSE)

list(rank = rank_X, betas = drop(beta), SSE = SSE)
```

